AxB represents the Cartesian product of sets A and B, which consists of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a is an element of A and b is an element of B. 

AxB = {(1,2), (1,4)}

BxA represents the Cartesian product of sets B and A, which consists of all ordered pairs (b, a) where b is an element of B and a is an element of A.

BxA = {(2,1), (4,1)}

As we can see, AxB and BxA are not equal because their ordered pairs are different:

